This article provides a background briefing on a phone call between President Obama and President Rouhani of Iran. The call took place in 2013 and lasted around 15 minutes. President Obama congratulated President Rouhani on his election and expressed the opportunity for progress on resolving the nuclear issue. The bulk of the call focused on the nuclear issue, with both leaders agreeing to work towards an agreement in consultation with the P5-plus-1. They also discussed the importance of building trust and the potential for a deeper relationship between the United States and Iran. The call also touched on the concern for three American citizens held in Iran. The article also addresses questions about the dynamics of the call, the use of social media by President Rouhani, and the potential impact on U.S.-Israeli relations.